# robots: noindex — system rules

## Pages that must always have `robots: { index: false }`

The following route categories must **never** be crawled or indexed. Apply this to the `export const metadata` (or `generateMetadata`) in every matching page file, **without exception**.

### Always noindex

| Category | Route pattern | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Comparison flow | `/compare/build` | Internal step page, no standalone value |
| Comparison results | `/compare/results` | Personalised, session-specific, duplicate risk |
| Any future checkout | `/checkout/**`, `/order/**` | Transactional, no SEO value |
| Account / auth | `/account/**`, `/login`, `/signup`, `/dashboard/**` | Private user pages |
| Any preview/debug | `?preview=true` or `/preview/**` | Development/QA only |

### `/compare` landing page

`/compare` (the marketing landing page) **is** indexable — it is a product page, not a user-specific or internal page. Do **not** add `robots: { index: false }` here.

## Implementation

```ts
// Correct — in any page file that falls under the categories above:
export const metadata = {
  title: "...",
  robots: { index: false },
};

// Or via generateMetadata:
export async function generateMetadata() {
  return {
    title: "...",
    robots: { index: false },
  };
}
```

## Checklist

- [ ] Every new page under `/compare/build`, `/compare/results` has `robots: { index: false }`.
- [ ] Every future account, login, signup, dashboard, checkout page has `robots: { index: false }`.
- [ ] `/compare` landing page does **not** have `robots: { index: false }`.
- [ ] Do not set `robots: { index: false }` on any city guide, country hub, blog post, or `/destinations` — those are public SEO pages.
